Use the standard library
This is how to match_parens of lst:
   Remember that balance is 0
   Remember that i is 0
   Do this lst's length times:
      Remember that part is item i in lst
      Remember that j is 0
      Do this part's length times:
         Remember that c is item j in part
         When c is 40, then:
            Increase balance
         End when
         When c is 41, then:
            Decrease balance
            When balance is less than 0, then:
               The answer is "No"
            End when
         End when
         When c is "(", then:
            Increase balance
         End when
         When c is ")", then:
            Decrease balance
            When balance is less than 0, then:
               The answer is "No"
            End when
         End when
         Increase j
      End do
      Increase i
   End do
   When balance is 0, then:
      The answer is "Yes"
   End when
   The answer is "No"
